{
  "texts": [
    "This tradition makes room for and indeed realistically expects (at least periodically) invalid proofs (the history of mathematics having seen many), just as the tradition of computer programming makes plenty of room for programs that are invalid (but certainly programs).",
    "In point of fact, we ourselves, in adopting a thoroughgoing inferencetheoretic perspective, regard arguments to be akin to proofs and After all, program verification makes little sense if there cannot be programs that are invalid.",
    "For discussion of this, see Arkoudas and Bringsjord .",
    "For a paradigm of program verification based directly on our brand of logicist AI, see Bringsjord .",
    "The timeline."
  ]
}